Many runs on rafflesia¶

  • 99 sub-samplings of the data
  • 99 replicate reuns with perturbed parameters
  • 4 models each

Each output is a list. The filds are:

  1. model number (0,1,2)
  2. SFS number (0-98)
  3. random seed
  4. model output (list)
    1. best parametrs
    2. LL
    3. etc
  5. run time

In [73]:
fits0 = [i for i in fits if i[0] == 0]
fits1 = [i for i in fits if i[0] == 1]
fits2 = [i for i in fits if i[0] == 2]
fits3 = [i for i in fits if i[0] == 3]

Each of these has 99 replicate fits for the same SFS, select the best ones for each SFS.

In [74]:
bestfits0 = []
bestfits1 = []
bestfits2 = []
bestfits3 = []
for i in range(99):
    bf0temp = [j for j in fits0 if j[1] == i]
    LL0temp = [j[3][1] for j in bf0temp]
    bestfits0.append(bf0temp[np.where(LL0temp == np.min(LL0temp))[0][0]])
    
    bf1temp = [j for j in fits1 if j[1] == i]
    LL1temp = [j[3][1] for j in bf1temp]
    bestfits1.append(bf1temp[np.where(LL1temp == np.min(LL1temp))[0][0]])
    
    bf2temp = [j for j in fits2 if j[1] == i]
    LL2temp = [j[3][1] for j in bf2temp]
    bestfits2.append(bf2temp[np.where(LL2temp == np.min(LL2temp))[0][0]])
    
    bf3temp = [j for j in fits3 if j[1] == i]
    LL3temp = [j[3][1] for j in bf3temp]
    bestfits3.append(bf2temp[np.where(LL3temp == np.min(LL3temp))[0][0]])

Create an numpy array from the items of fits (using only the 1st slot of each).

The cols are 0 (const GF): nuT, nuD, mTD, mDT, T0
old GF 1: nuT, nuD, mTD, mDT, T0, T1
no GF 2: nuT, nuD, T0
